        "message" : [
          "%md",
          "### Number of rows per `MATCH` ",
          "",
          "The default behavior of a MATCH clause is to return one row per match of the pattern.  ",
          "Often however we want to list the individual vertices or edges especially when the match returns a path as in the query above.  ",
          "",
          "In the following query we use the ONE ROW PER STEP modifier to list each edge so that we can list the vertices and edges or visualize the path. ",
          "",
          "See the [PGQL language specification](https://pgql-lang.org/spec/1.5/#number-of-rows-per-match) for details. "
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "html",
        "visualizationConfig" : null,
        "hideCode" : true,
        "hideResult" : false,
        "hideGutter" : true,
        "hideVizConfig" : false,
        "hideInIFrame" : false,
        "enabled" : true,
        "forms" : "[]",
        "result" : {
          "startTime" : 1661453171787,
          "endTime" : 1661453171861,
          "interpreter" : "md",
          "taskStatus" : "SUCCESS",
          "status" : "SUCCESS",
          "results" : [
            {
              "message" : "<h3 id=\"number-of-rows-per-match\">Number of rows per <code>MATCH</code></h3>\n<p>The default behavior of a MATCH clause is to return one row per match of the pattern.<br />\nOften however we want to list the individual vertices or edges especially when the match returns a path as in the query above.</p>\n<p>In the following query we use the ONE ROW PER STEP modifier to list each edge so that we can list the vertices and edges or visualize the path.</p>\n<p>See the <a href=\"https://pgql-lang.org/spec/1.5/#number-of-rows-per-match\">PGQL language specification</a> for details.</p>\n",
              "type" : "HTML"
            }
          ],
          "forms" : null
        },
        "relations" : [ ],
        "dynamicFormParams" : "{}"
      },
      {
        "row" : 0,
        "col" : 0,
        "sizeX" : 0,
        "width" : 12,
        "title" : null,
        "hasTitle" : false,
        "message" : [
          "%pgql-pgx",
          "/* the element_number() function returns a sequence number for each vertex or edge in a matching graph pattern. ",
          "The count starts with a vertex so vertices have odd numbers and edges will have even numbers */",
          "SELECT element_number(v) as First_Vertex, element_number(e1) as Connecting_Edge, element_number(v2) as Intermediate_Vertex, id(v), id(e1), id(v2)",
          "from match any shortest (c1:CUSTOMERS) (-[e]-(p:SALES|PRODUCTS|CUSTOMERS))+(c2:CUSTOMERS) on sh_pgview_graph  ONE ROW PER STEP (v,e1,v2)",
          "where c1.cust_id=6319 and c2.cust_id=100344 order by First_Vertex"
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "table",
        "visualizationConfig" : "[{\"table\":{\"numberOfItems\":8,\"lastColumns\":[\"match_number(v)\",\"id(v)\",\"id(e1)\",\"id(v2)\"],\"version\":1}}]",
